In Angular, a shared component is a component that can be used across multiple modules and is usually a piece of UI that can be reused throughout your application.

Here are the steps to create a shared component in Angular:

**Step 1: Create a new directory for your shared components**

In your Angular project, create a new directory called `shared` (or any other name you prefer) to hold your shared components. This will help keep your shared components organized and separate from your other components.

**Step 2: Create a new component**

In your `shared` directory, create a new component by running the following command:
```
ng generate component <component-name>
```
Replace `<component-name>` with the name of your component, for example, `my-shared-component`.

**Step 3: Define the component**

In the `my-shared-component` component file (`my-shared-component.component.ts`), define the component:
```typescript
import { Component, Input } from '@angular/core';

@Component({
  selector: 'app-my-shared-component',
  templateUrl: './my-shared-component.component.html',
  styleUrls: ['./my-shared-component.component.css']
})
export class MySharedComponent {
  @Input() title: string;
}
```
In this example, we're defining a simple component with an `@Input` property called `title`.

**Step 4: Create the component template**

In the `my-shared-component` component directory, create a new file called `my-shared-component.component.html`. This file will contain the HTML template for your component:
```html
<h1>{{ title }}</h1>
```
This template will display the `title` property passed to the component using the `{{ }}` syntax.

**Step 5: Add the component to the module**

In your `app.module.ts` file, add the shared component to the imports array:
```typescript
import { NgModule } from '@angular/core';
import { CommonModule } from '@angular/common';
import { MySharedComponent } from './shared/my-shared-component/my-shared-component.component';

@NgModule({
  declarations: [MySharedComponent],
  imports: [CommonModule],
  exports: [MySharedComponent]
})
export class AppModule {}
```
In this example, we're declaring the `MySharedComponent` and exporting it so that it can be used in other modules.

